    "path": ".smithers/prompts/create-workflow-fix.mdx",
    "contents": "# Fix the workflow until its graph renders\n\nThe new workflow failed to render its graph. `smithers graph` loads the module\n(catching TypeScript / import / JSX errors) and renders one frame without\nexecuting it (catching structural errors). Read the error, fix the files, and\nmake it load. You have file + shell tools.\n\n## Workflow\n\n- Name: {props.workflowName}\n- Entry file: {props.workflowFile}\n\n## Verify command that failed\n\n`bunx smithers-orchestrator graph {props.workflowFile}`\n\n## Errors\n\n{JSON.stringify(props.errors, null, 2)}\n\n## Intended design (the source of truth for behaviour)\n\n{JSON.stringify(props.design, null, 2)}\n\n## How to fix\n\n1. Read the entry file and any prompt/component files it imports.\n2. Map the error to a cause. Common ones:\n   - **Import / module not found** — a prompt or component path is wrong, or a\n     named export doesn't exist. Check `{props.promptsDir}` and `../components`.\n   - **Type / schema error** — a `<Task output={outputs.x}>` doesn't match its\n     Zod schema, or a destructured component (`Branch`, `Loop`, `Approval`) was\n     never pulled out of `createSmithers(...)`.\n   - **JSX / structural** — a conditional renders the wrong child type, a node id\n     is duplicated, or a control-flow component is missing a required prop\n     (`Loop` needs `until`; `Approval` needs `request`).\n3. Make the smallest change that fixes the error without abandoning the design.\n   If the docs would help, run `bunx smithers-orchestrator docs` or\n   `bunx smithers-orchestrator ask \"<question>\"`.\n4. Re-run `bunx smithers-orchestrator graph {props.workflowFile}` yourself to\n   confirm it now exits 0 before you finish.\n\nDo not delete the workflow or stub it out to \"pass\" — fix the real problem.\n\n## Output\n\nReturn the files you changed as `filesWritten` (path + kind) and a one-line\n`summary` of the fix.\n\nREQUIRED OUTPUT:\n{props.schema}\n"
